1
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:08,280
Didn't you say it was urgent?

2
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:09,800
It is urgent.

3
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,400
I just missed you.

4
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,160
The company's finances are bad lately.

5
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:23,320
I'm stressed out.

6
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,960
You've made plenty of money from me.

7
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,520
I told you.

8
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:38,160
Make Wenxin the legal representative,

9
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,360
let her take the fall,

10
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,160
and we can run away together.

11
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:44,940
But you wouldn't do it.

12
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:48,760
I came up with another plan for you.

13
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:51,640
Once Wenxin is dead

14
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:54,160
and we get the money,

15
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,840
what else do you have to worry about?

16
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,530
Why are you here?

17
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,480
Sun Wen.

18
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,180
Sun Wen, are you there?

19
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,400
Sun Wen, can you hear me?

20
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:28,600
Sun Wen.

21
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,480
Sun Wen.

22
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,479
Sun Wen, listen to me.

23
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:35,479
You're in danger tonight. Be very careful.

24
00:01:37,479 --> 00:01:39,009
Hiding a mistress, are you?

25
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:41,780
I'm going to see where you've hidden her.

26
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,280
Sun Wen, can you hear me?

27
00:01:45,479 --> 00:01:46,280
Sun Wen.

28
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,320
Sun Wen, answer me if you can hear me.

29
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:53,080
Do you believe in parallel universes?

30
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:56,410
Parallel spacetime is also known as the multiverse theory.

31
00:01:56,479 --> 00:01:58,520
Apart from this universe we humans inhabit,

32
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:00,520
there may be other universes.

33
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,240
Of our 2,000 revolving lanterns,

34
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,800
do you remember the one we sold?

35
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,960
That's the one.

36
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,740
It can connect to spacetime 12 days from now.

37
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,039
You must not go to the hotel you're planning to visit.

38
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,120
Or else you'll die.

39
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,450
The bastard really wasn't lying to me.

40
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,360
Are you crazy?

41
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:14,920
What are you doing?

42
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,640
Why are you acting crazy this late at night?

43
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:17,680
I'm crazy?

44
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,760
I was crazy to go to the hotel to save you.

45
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,120
I didn't believe it at first.

46
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,050
But this lamp...

47
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,920
The lamp spoke.

48
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,440
She said you were at that hotel.

49
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,800
Fine, so I went.

50
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,160
And you were actually there.

51
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,680
There really is a time reversal rescue.

52
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,800
There really are people from 12 days in the future.

53
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,280
There really is a multiverse.

54
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,880
Yes, I told you before.

55
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,079
It can talk.

56
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,800
Talk? Talk about what?

57
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:37,720
Talk, my ass.

58
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,520
Reset, my ass.

59
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,360
From now on,

60
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,730
everything is fake.

61
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,640
We're both sick.

62
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,570
We're both sick.

63
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,760
These are all hallucinations.

64
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,400
Promise me you won't get involved anymore.

65
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,200
Okay?

66
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,480
I can't.

67
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,740
I promised Wenxin.

68
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,360
I must save her husband and child.

69
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,620
Then who will save you?

70
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,280
What do you mean?

71
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,480
You won't always get this lucky.

72
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,410
Do you know that?

73
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,050
If I hadn't been here today,

74
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,720
you...

75
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,529
you would have died.

76
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,400
We've been together since college.

77
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,530
It's been six years.

78
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,000
I support whatever you do.

79
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,040
But this time,

80
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,720
So this time,

81
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,280
you still have to support me.

82
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:54,680
You...

83
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,040
Wenxin must be desperate right now.

84
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,360
I'm her only hope.

85
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,040
If I don't help her,

86
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,440
You save her, but who saves you?

87
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,160
You do.

88
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:22,880
Me?

89
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,480
But you might die.

90
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:47,600
I know.

91
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,560
Are you sure

92
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,680
you have to be this hero?

93
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,120
I'm sure.

94
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,440
I must be this hero.

95
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:07,560
Okay.

96
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,360
Since I can't talk you out of it,

97
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,960
I'll risk my life to join you.

98
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:13,880
Really?

99
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,290
But first things first,

100
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,580
there is something we must do.

101
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,120
All right. What is it? Let's go.

102
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,200
Sleep. I'm exhausted.

103
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,520
I'm so sleepy.

104
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,720
Wake up.

105
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:51,920
Don't sleep.

106
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,680
Don't sleep.

107
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,360
Get up.

108
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,580
What time is it?

109
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,440
I don't know.

110
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,960
I'm sorry.

111
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,080
Okay, I'm up.

112
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,580
We haven't started on yesterday's plan yet.

113
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,480
Go ahead.

114
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,280
From what you're saying,

115
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,400
you're the only one who can save

116
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,200
Wenxin's husband and daughter.

117
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,320
Tomorrow.

118
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,320
Tomorrow is the day of the car accident.

119
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,600
And I know something else.

120
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,720
Wenxin's husband

121
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:32,400
is plotting with his mistress to kill Wenxin

122
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,820
to use the compensation to cover his company's losses.

123
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,880
Those scumbags.

124
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,880
We have to tell Wenxin.

125
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,140
I want to tell her, too.

126
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:43,680
But the Wenxin in this timeline...

127
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,040
would never believe a word I say.

128
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:46,970
It's too absurd.

129
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,650
Telling her would only push her further away.

130
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,200
The only way is for Wenxin to save herself.

131
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,930
She doesn't believe me anyway.

132
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,220
Midnight tonight.

133
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,880
Is there one more chance to make a call?

134
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,600
Why don't you ask the Wenxin from 12 days later

135
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,280
if there are any...

136
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,880
secrets only she would know.

137
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,360
For instance,

138
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,560
that she actually hates her mother-in-law.

139
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,560
And even wants to tear her mouth off.

140
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,960
Or maybe,

141
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:25,440
that her sex life with her husband...

142
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,880
is actually terrible.

143
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,800
But she can never say it.

144
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,800
So,

145
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,039
That's pretty mean.

146
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,480
Stop giving me terrible ideas.

147
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,159
Right?

148
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,400
But the ultimate goal

149
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:39,159
is to get this timeline's Wenxin to trust you.

150
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:39,600
Right?

151
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,280
Yeah.

152
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,250
But we're short on time.

153
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,240
I'll figure something out with Wenxin.

154
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,360
I have another job for you.

155
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:45,960
What is it?

156
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,360
This number

157
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,600
belongs to the other party in the crash.

158
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,120
The truck driver.

159
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,920
If he doesn't drive by that spot that afternoon,

160
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,450
the accident won't happen.

161
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,010
I'll handle Wenxin.

162
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:00,880
You handle the truck driver.

163
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,120
Attention!

164
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,410
Reporting, sir.

165
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,960
Consider it done.

166
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:08,760
Go on.

167
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:20,600
Sun Wen.

168
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,520
I'm here.

169
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:22,800
I only remember

170
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,560
sending you to the security room.

171
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,720
How did you end up having an accident at the hotel?

172
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,040
Let's not talk about that now.

173
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,200
Time is tight.

174
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,400
Today is the day of the accident.

175
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,840
So the most important thing right now

176
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,520
is to stop the accident.

177
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:36,360
Yes.

178
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:39,120
Today is the last chance.

179
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:39,920
Listen to me.

180
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:42,120
Is there anything that only you know?

181
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,360
Like you don't get along with your mother-in-law,

182
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,000
and you want to tear her mouth apart.

183
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:46,800
Or...

184
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,760
you and your husband,

185
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,930
are just... in that department...

186
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,410
You know what I mean?

187
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,880
My husband and I...

188
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,320
It's fine.

189
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,400
Just tell me something

190
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,480
that only you know.

191
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,160
Then I'll tell the you in this timeline,

192
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,890
something that will make you believe me for sure.

193
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:03,720
Anything?

194
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,000
It's the last chance.

195
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,490
We must succeed.

196
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:11,360
We can't fail.

197
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:13,520
Yes.

198
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,520
Honey, Xixi.

199
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,280
Wait a moment.

200
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,340
I'll be right down.

201
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:25,360
Wen Xin.

202
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,520
You again?

203
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,600
What exactly do you want?

204
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,960
I'm really not a bad guy.

205
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,920
I just want to save your husband and daughter.

206
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:32,600
Today,

207
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,960
you'll have an accident on Guanhu Avenue.

208
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,440
Your husband and daughter will die.

209
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,200
So you must not go today.

210
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,860
You're still talking?

211
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,600
Shut up!

212
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,520
Shut up!

213
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,040
You!

214
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,760
Give me a minute.

215
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,040
Let me show you something,

216
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,800
then you'll believe me, okay?

217
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,160
Look at me.

218
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:57,320
Flowers...

219
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,600
Bloom...

220
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,000
Baby...

221
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,200
Be good...

222
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,640
The night...

223
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:03,680
no matter how dark,

224
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:05,340
The night, no matter how dark,

225
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,760
I am here.

226
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,880
Flowers bloom,

227
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,720
baby be good.

228
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:12,800
The night, no matter how dark,

229
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,360
I am here.

230
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:32,760
Believe him.

231
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,440
You must believe him.
